From: Calculinux <noreply@calculinux.org>
Subject: [PATCH] librsvg: fix native configure finding cairo (pkgconfig)

librsvg-native do_configure fails with "Run-time dependency cairo found: NO"
because the recipe exports EXTRA_NATIVE_PKGCONFIG_PATH with only
${B}/meson-uninstalled, so pkg-config never searches the native sysroot
where cairo-native is staged. Prepend the native sysroot pkgconfig path.

Signed-off-by: Calculinux <noreply@calculinux.org>
---
 recipes-gnome/librsvg/librsvg_2.61.3.bb | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/recipes-gnome/librsvg/librsvg_2.61.3.bb b/recipes-gnome/librsvg/librsvg_2.61.3.bb
--- a/recipes-gnome/librsvg/librsvg_2.61.3.bb
+++ b/recipes-gnome/librsvg/librsvg_2.61.3.bb
@@ -38,7 +38,7 @@ BASEDEPENDS:append = " cargo-native"
 # for cargo to be happy
 BASEDEPENDS:append = " cargo-native"
 
-export EXTRA_NATIVE_PKGCONFIG_PATH = "${B}/meson-uninstalled:"
+export EXTRA_NATIVE_PKGCONFIG_PATH = "${STAGING_LIBDIR_NATIVE}/pkgconfig:${B}/meson-uninstalled:"
 export RUST_BACKTRACE = "full"
 export RUSTFLAGS
 
